---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Standard Photo Print Sizes: Complete Guide to Every Print Dimension 2025"
  description="Complete guide to standard photo print sizes. Learn about common print dimensions, square photo prints, photo print size charts, and how to resize photos for perfect prints."
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 mt-[80px] md:mt-10">

    <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
    <nav class="mb-8">
      <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
        <li><a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a></li>
        <li><span class="text-gray-400">/</span></li>
        <li><a href="/blogs" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Blog</a></li>
        <li><span class="text-gray-400">/</span></li>
        <li class="text-gray-900">Standard Photo Print Sizes</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <div class="mb-6">
      <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-primary text-white text-sm font-crimson font-medium rounded-full">
        Guides
      </span>
    </div>

    <h1 class="font-crimson text-[40px] md:text-[60px] leading-tight text-gray-900 mb-6">
      Standard Photo Print Sizes: Complete Guide to Every Print Dimension
    </h1>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4 text-gray-600 mb-8 pb-8 border-b-2 border-gray-200">
      <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 7V3m8 4V3m-9 8h10M5 21h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z"></path>
        </svg>
        <span>February 25, 2026</span>
      </div>
      <span class="text-gray-400">•</span>
      <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
        </svg>
        <span>10 min read</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Featured Image -->
    <div class="mb-12 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
      <img
        src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1516035069371-29a1b244cc32?w=1200&h=600&fit=crop"
        alt="Standard photo print sizes — photos and prints guide"
        class="w-full h-auto"
        width="1200"
        height="600"
        loading="eager"
      />
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tertiary to-green-50 border-2 border-secondary/30 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-0">
          Ordering photo prints that come back blurry, cropped wrong, or in the wrong size is frustrating and wasteful. This complete guide covers every standard photo print size — including inches, centimeters, and the exact pixel dimensions needed at 300 DPI for sharp results.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Complete Photo Print Size Chart</h2>

      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mb-8">
        <table class="w-full">
          <thead class="bg-gradient-to-r from-tertiary to-green-50">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-5 py-4 text-left font-crimson text-lg text-gray-900">Size (inches)</th>
              <th class="px-5 py-4 text-left font-crimson text-lg text-gray-900">Size (cm)</th>
              <th class="px-5 py-4 text-left font-crimson text-lg text-gray-900">Pixels at 300 DPI</th>
              <th class="px-5 py-4 text-left font-crimson text-lg text-gray-900">Best Use</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            <tr><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">3.5×5"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">9×13 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">1050×1500</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Wallet, keepsake</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">4×4"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">10×10 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">1200×1200</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Square print, Instagram</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">4×6"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">10×15 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">1200×1800</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Snapshots, most popular</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">5×5"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">13×13 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">1500×1500</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Square photo print</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">5×7"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">13×18 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">1500×2100</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Portraits, gifts</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">6×6"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">15×15 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">1800×1800</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Square photo print</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">8×8"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">20×20 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">2400×2400</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Square wall art</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">8×10"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">20×25 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">2400×3000</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Portraits, school photos</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">8×12"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">20×30 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">2400×3600</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">DSLR native (3:2 ratio)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">10×10"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">25×25 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">3000×3000</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Square wall art</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">11×14"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">28×35 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">3300×4200</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Wall art, portraits</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">12×12"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">30×30 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">3600×3600</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Square album art</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">12×18"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">30×45 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">3600×5400</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Large landscape print</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">16×20"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">40×50 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">4800×6000</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Large wall display</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">18×24"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">46×61 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">5400×7200</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Poster / art print</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">20×24"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">51×61 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">6000×7200</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Large portrait</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">24×36"</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">61×91 cm</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">7200×10800</td><td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700">Poster, large art</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Most Common Photo Print Sizes</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8">The most ordered print sizes depend on the use case. Here's a breakdown by category:</p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tertiary to-green-50 border-2 border-secondary/30 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl text-gray-900 mb-3">🏠 Everyday Prints</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex justify-between"><span><strong>4×6"</strong></span><span class="text-gray-500">Most popular</span></li>
            <li class="flex justify-between"><span><strong>5×7"</strong></span><span class="text-gray-500">Gifts, portraits</span></li>
            <li class="flex justify-between"><span><strong>8×10"</strong></span><span class="text-gray-500">School photos</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tertiary to-green-50 border-2 border-secondary/30 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl text-gray-900 mb-3">🖼️ Wall Art Prints</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex justify-between"><span><strong>11×14"</strong></span><span class="text-gray-500">Medium wall</span></li>
            <li class="flex justify-between"><span><strong>16×20"</strong></span><span class="text-gray-500">Statement piece</span></li>
            <li class="flex justify-between"><span><strong>18×24"</strong></span><span class="text-gray-500">Large print</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tertiary to-green-50 border-2 border-secondary/30 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl text-gray-900 mb-3">⬛ Square Prints</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex justify-between"><span><strong>4×4"</strong></span><span class="text-gray-500">Small square</span></li>
            <li class="flex justify-between"><span><strong>8×8"</strong></span><span class="text-gray-500">Medium square</span></li>
            <li class="flex justify-between"><span><strong>12×12"</strong></span><span class="text-gray-500">Album art, décor</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Square Photo Prints: Everything You Need to Know</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Square photo prints have surged in popularity thanks to Instagram and the rise of square album art. They work particularly well as gallery wall elements because you can rotate them in any direction and they still balance with rectangular frames.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mb-8">
        <table class="w-full">
          <thead class="bg-gradient-to-r from-tertiary to-green-50">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-crimson text-lg text-gray-900">Square Size</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-crimson text-lg text-gray-900">Pixels (300 DPI)</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-crimson text-lg text-gray-900">Best For</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            <tr><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">4×4"</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">1200 × 1200</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Cards, keepsakes</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">5×5"</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">1500 × 1500</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Instagram, gifts</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">8×8"</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">2400 × 2400</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Gallery wall accent</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">10×10"</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">3000 × 3000</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Statement wall art</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">12×12"</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">3600 × 3600</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Album cover display</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">What Resolution Do I Need for a Good Print?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Print quality is measured in <strong>DPI (dots per inch)</strong>. For sharp photo prints, you need <strong>300 DPI</strong> at the final print size. Minimum acceptable is 150 DPI but you'll see pixelation at larger sizes.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-2 border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <div class="flex items-start space-x-3">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
          </svg>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-crimson text-lg font-medium text-blue-900 mb-2">DPI Formula</h4>
            <p class="text-blue-800 text-sm">
              <strong>Required pixels = print size (inches) × DPI</strong><br/>
              For a 5×7" print at 300 DPI: 5×300 = 1,500px wide, 7×300 = 2,100px tall → you need at least 1500×2100 pixels.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">TikTok Profile Picture Size</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        TikTok profile pictures display at <strong>200×200 pixels</strong> but should be uploaded at a minimum of <strong>400×400 pixels</strong> (1:1 square ratio) for sharpness on high-DPI screens. The image is displayed as a circle on most TikTok pages, so keep your subject centered.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mb-8">
        <table class="w-full">
          <thead class="bg-gradient-to-r from-tertiary to-green-50">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-crimson text-lg text-gray-900">Platform</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-crimson text-lg text-gray-900">Profile Size (upload)</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-crimson text-lg text-gray-900">Displayed As</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            <tr><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">TikTok</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">400 × 400 px</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Circle</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Instagram</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">320 × 320 px</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Circle</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Facebook</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">170 × 170 px</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Circle</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Twitter / X</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">400 × 400 px</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Circle</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">YouTube</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">800 × 800 px</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Circle</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">LinkedIn</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">400 × 400 px</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Circle</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Discord</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">128 × 128 px</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Circle</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">How to Prepare a Photo for Print</h2>
      <ol class="space-y-6 mb-8">
        <li class="flex items-start space-x-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-white font-crimson font-bold">1</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">Check your pixel count</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Use the table above to verify you have enough pixels for your chosen print size at 300 DPI. A 12 megapixel phone camera (4000×3000px) is sufficient for an 8×10" print at 300 DPI.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start space-x-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-white font-crimson font-bold">2</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">Crop to the correct aspect ratio</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Crop your image to match the target print's aspect ratio before ordering. The print lab will crop it if you don't — and they may cut off your subject.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start space-x-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-white font-crimson font-bold">3</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">Export as sRGB JPEG</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Most print labs use the sRGB color space. Export your file as a JPEG at 85–95% quality in sRGB to avoid unexpected color shifts in the final print.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-2 border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <div class="flex items-start space-x-3">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
          </svg>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-crimson text-lg font-medium text-blue-900 mb-2">Resize in seconds</h4>
            <p class="text-blue-800 text-sm">
              Use our free <a href="/resize" class="underline font-medium hover:text-blue-600">Image Resizer tool</a> to crop any photo to any standard print size with exact pixel dimensions. No software needed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tertiary to-green-50 border-2 border-secondary/30 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center">
        <h3 class="font-crimson text-2xl md:text-3xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Get Print-Ready Images in Seconds</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Use our free image resizer to prepare any photo for any standard print size. Resize, crop, and export at 300 DPI-equivalent dimensions instantly.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <a href="/resize" class="px-6 py-3 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-secondary hover:from-secondary hover:to-primary text-white rounded-xl font-crimson font-semibold transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-105 shadow-lg">
            Resize for Printing
          </a>
          <a href="/blogs" class="px-6 py-3 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 text-primary border-2 border-primary rounded-xl font-crimson font-semibold transition-all duration-300">
            More Guides
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Share Section -->
    <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t-2 border-gray-200">
      <p class="font-crimson text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 mb-4">Share this article</p>
      <div class="flex space-x-4">
        <button class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-secondary hover:from-secondary hover:to-primary text-white rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-110">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M24 12.073c0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12s-12 5.373-12 12c0 5.99 4.388 10.954 10.125 11.854v-8.385H7.078v-3.47h3.047V9.43c0-3.007 1.792-4.669 4.533-4.669 1.312 0 2.686.235 2.686.235v2.953H15.83c-1.491 0-1.956.925-1.956 1.874v2.25h3.328l-.532 3.47h-2.796v8.385C19.612 23.027 24 18.062 24 12.073z"/></svg>
        </button>
        <button class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-secondary hover:from-secondary hover:to-primary text-white rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-110">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M23.953 4.57a10 10 0 01-2.825.775 4.958 4.958 0 002.163-2.723c-.951.555-2.005.959-3.127 1.184a4.92 4.92 0 00-8.384 4.482C7.69 8.095 4.067 6.13 1.64 3.162a4.822 4.822 0 00-.666 2.475c0 1.71.87 3.213 2.188 4.096a4.904 4.904 0 01-2.228-.616v.06a4.923 4.923 0 003.946 4.827 4.996 4.996 0 01-2.212.085 4.936 4.936 0 004.604 3.417 9.867 9.867 0 01-6.102 2.105c-.39 0-.779-.023-1.17-.067a13.995 13.995 0 007.557 2.209c9.053 0 13.998-7.496 13.998-13.985 0-.21 0-.42-.015-.63A9.935 9.935 0 0024 4.59z"/></svg>
